#: mageia-cauldron opensuse-leap-15-4 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "\\(bu does not automatically hard-wrap lines that become overlong,"
msgstr ""
"\\(bu ne replie pas automatiquement physiquement les lignes qui deviennent "
"trop longues\\ ;"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-36 fedora-rawhide
#: mageia-cauldron opensuse-leap-15-4 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "\\(bu includes the line below the title bar in the editing area,"
msgstr ""
"\\(bu inclut la ligne située sous la ligne de titre dans l'espace "
"d'édition\\ ;"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-36 fedora-rawhide
#: mageia-cauldron opensuse-leap-15-4 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "\\(bu does linewise (smooth) scrolling."
msgstr "\\(bu applique un défilement progressif (ligne par ligne)."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-36 fedora-rawhide
#: mageia-cauldron opensuse-leap-15-4 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"If you want the old, Pico behavior back, you can use B<--breaklonglines>, "
"B<--emptyline>, and B<--jumpyscrolling> (or B<-bej> for short)."
msgstr ""
"Si vous souhaitez retourner au comportement ancien de Pico, vous pouvez "
"utiliser les options B<--breaklonglines>, B<--emptyline> et B<--"
"jumpyscrolling> (ou B<-bej> en raccourci)."

#. type: SH
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-36 fedora-rawhide
